race.description: Greg Driscoll Country Boosted Showcase Mdn Hcp
race.comment: REMY'S BRO (6) settled last in a small field on debut last start over 930m at this track before letting down in good style to grab second. Sure to appreciate the extra trip with that run under the belt. Penza should settle just off the pace then he will be charging home late. Happy to have him on top ahead of Locally trained VIVEK (11) comes off a seven-week let-up which followed some plain performances. Nicely drawn and if the pace is on as expected he could be the one getting home best. Stablemate REVOKE (2) didn't do a bad job on debut here recently and can improve with the shades going on. SILVER SERENADE (10) on debut for the Danny Williams stable did enough in a recent Goulburn trial to suggest she can run a bit of a race. A couple of other first starters in CANDO ATTITUDE (8) and STERN LOOKS (1) have been well found in early markets and should be monitored throughout betting for further support.
